::: {.callout-important}

# Conclusion

1. Inter-series variability does not seem to be simply ramdom errors but due to instrumental drift over the different analysis days. 
2. The LA-ICPMS processing method (baseline correction or not) needs to be adapted to each individual element
3. A correction equation needs to be established to further reduce inter-series variance.

:::


## Data correction methodology

Biases due to differences in ICPMS detector response to elemental concentrations can be reduced by standardising all sample sample series data to one reference series. This standardisation procedure is carried out by modelling the elemental signal measured for the Oak reference wood core in the reference sample series from the elemental signal measured for the Oak reference wood core in any other of the 11 series. @fig-inter-series-calibration_K shows the type of relationship between the two datasets. While close to linear a best fit is obtained with a second degree polynomial regression.


